==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incitation
<hw>In`ci*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incitatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incitation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of inciting or moving to action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which incites to action; that which rouses or
prompts; incitement; motive; incentive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The noblest <qex>incitation</qex> to honest attempts.</q>
<rj><qau>Tatler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incitative</ent>⟦br⟧
